modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve and parse CPU information, including core count, model name, and cache sizes from system files. Operates on strings and integers, extracting structured data from raw text outputs. Used to gather hardware details for performance monitoring and system diagnostics.

Returns the number of active CPU cores and allows pinning the current process to a specific core. Operates on integer values representing core indices. Used to control process execution affinity and optimize parallel task distribution.
